### 2.0.17

** NOTICE: This release has been taken down from PivNet**
* A bug in OpsManager causes PAS's Diego cells to fail to trust all of the appropriate TLS certificates which were previously trusted before upgrading OpsManager.
The full impact of the bug has not yet been confirmed, but it is known that it is possible for this bug to additionally affect other tiles.  
Specifically, it will affect tiles where the author of the tile, inside the tile's YAML definition file, has used a multiline string which contains multiple double-parenthesis expressions within the multi-line string.  
The bug will cause these to render incorrectly in the BOSH manifest for the tile.  
These multi-line strings containing multiple double-parenthesis expressions are typically used by tile authors to construct certificate chains for their BOSH manifests.
*The following is an example of a portion of a tile's YAML file which will be effected by this bug:
      trusted_certs: |
          ((( /cf/diego-instance-identity-root-ca.certificate )))
          (( $ops_manager.ca_certificate ))
          (( $ops_manager.trusted_certificates ))

* **[Bug Fix]**: You can now delete an unused AZ in an installation after clicking **Apply Changes**.
* **[Feature Improvement]**: Installation Dashboard and deployment status pages may load more quickly.
* **[Security Fix]**: Bumps Nokogiri to 1.8.4 to remediate [CVE-2017-15412](https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2017-15412).

